Feb 28 2007 	A comfortable stay	I didn't know quite what to expect knowing the age of this hotel (I last stayed in it 26 years ago!), but we found it to be elegant, professional, with an extremely friendly and helpful staff. Every worker we encountered seemed to want to do all he or she could to ensure we had a great stay. I was pleasantly surprised by some of the little services, like offering to give us a follow-up wake up call ten minutes after the first call.The entire hotel, both common areas and our room, was furnished with lovely colors, textures, and furniture. All very comfortable, clean, and classy. The bathroom was the only place I noticed the hotel's age.The hotel seems to cater more to the business and convention traveler. Frequent shuttles to the airport and convention center looked to be very handy.With our own car, we didn't take advantage of the shuttles. We were surprised to pay $20 a night for parking with in/out privileges. We were also surprised to find the high speed internet is $12.95 plus tax each day. Our business schedule was packed so the only facility we were able to try was the restaurant for breakfast each morning. The service was top-notch.All in all we had a comfortable stay.	
Dec 2 2006 	Near-luxury large hotel	I was there Fri-Sun for a meeting held at the hotel. The first nice touch was a free shuttle from O'Hare that picks up every 30 minutes. Check-in was friendly and efficient - they make you aware this is a nonsmoking hotel. The room was quite a long walk away from the lobby - lots of hallways, corners - easy to get lost! Everything was clean and modern as in most Marriotts, and the bed was comfortable. A small patio looked out over the indoor/outdoor pool. This was neat at first but I couldn't go to sleep early because noisy kids were swimming until about 10 PM.There's a bar and a couple of restaurants. I had dinner at the Champion grill - a sports-themed place with countless big-screen TVs on the walls all tuned to different games. The food was good and reasonably priced. Meeting rooms were average. I visited the fitness room, which had plenty of equipment and individual TVs and free earphones on the cardio machines.I had a break so I wanted to take a walk in the neighborhood. The bell desk was helpful but said there was nothing to do or see around the hotel unless I wanted to take a cab or the train in to the city. I walked around anyway, and as they said there wasn't anything interesting to see or do. There is a large grocery store about a block away and I picked up a few snacks to eat in the room.The shuttle returned to the airport on schedule, rounding out a nice trip. In summary, this hotel is great for business in the area and there were a number of families having a good time, especially in the pool/spa area.	
