Jul 31 2006 	Comfortable but needs updating	Stayed one night in July 2006 for business. The room as well as the hotel in general are acceptable, but not up to the standards of the typical Marriott. The facilities seem to be rather old, and in need of more than a superficial redecorating.My room was on the ground floor in a wing overlooking the pool. I was nervous about noise, but this was not a problem once evening came. The bed was very comfortable with bountiful pillows and comforters. The furniture and carpeting looked to be well worn but clean. The only cleaning flaw I could see were &quot;dust bunnies&quot; in the corners of the bathroom floor (under the counter). I had difficulty adjusting the thermostat in the room -- the only choices seemed to be to blast the air conditioning to arctic level or endure dampness/humidity that left the mirror fogged (this was long before I took a shower, I should note!). Internet access is available for a fee.I didn't eat any meals at the hotel so I can't speak to their food offerings. I got a snack at the gift shop which has plenty of drinks and healthy snacks available.My colleague and I found the front desk staff to be somewhat less than helpful when we were seeking restaurant recommendations. The employee handed us a mimeographed sheets with restaurant options, but really couldn't tell us what was near or far, although she told us none were in walking distance.Airport-Hotel shuttle: We waited over half an hour at the airport bus area -- the shuttle seems to service a number of hotels so it can be slow at peak times.The CTA Blue Line is right next to the hotel premises. It was very easy to get downtown.Overall, it's okay, but a little less than I would expect from Marriott.	
