May 2 2006	Great Staff Still Feels Dingy	Despite their best efforts to make this hotel adhere to Marriott standards, this hotel falls a bit short. Despite furniture typical for the chain, the rooms were only fair. Little irritations such as walking into the room and finding the temperature to be somehwere north of 80 degrees (heat set on high). The hallways felt dim and underlit, and not in a fashionable way. My room was an unreasonably long walk from the lobby, as you have to walk throught the pool atrium (!). Most people would find it to be an approximately 10 minute walk. The staff was surpisingly pleasant and helpful even by Marriott standards. The food in the restaurant was decent but typically pricey. The airport shuttle leaves every 15 minutes and was on-time. The room internet access was $12/day and wired only (not wireless), so there's no surfing from bed . Overall, I felt that the Orbitz room rate ~$145 was a decent value for this hotel. A luxurious rest spot it isn't, but it is a reasonable place to crash near O'Hare.	
