Apr 10 2005 	Not too shabby	I stayed at the Mariott because I was participating in a music festival with my high school concert band. The lobby is nice, and there's a lot of conference rooms and a place where you can make copies and send things. Be sure to check out the map of the hotel - if you don't find the elevator closer to your room, it could mean a lot of unnecessary walking. I had a room with two double beds, and they were kind of small, but they're able to fit two average-sized people. The bathroom is kind of small also, and there's no ventilation system, but its clean - no mildew or anything. The pool is a lot better than most hotels - there's a glass dome, and you can swim outside or inside in one big pool. The maids and front desk were nice, and fulfilled all of my requests. The hotel has some drawbacks but overall it is a good place to stay. I would rate it 3.5 stars if that was possible.	
Mar 1 2005	Just Okay - There are Better Choices	My husband and I stayed at the Marriott O'Hare at the end of February 2005, when we were stranded in Chicago for the night due to a cancelled flight to Boston (weather delays). A convenient shuttle bus runs between the hotel and the airport every 15-20 minutes and the hotel is about a 10 minute ride from the airport. This is definately a hotel geared to the business traveller and is also used for many conferences and business meetings. There is nothing charming or interesting about this hotel, in either the public areas or the rooms. It's pretty much just a big ugly box. The ceilings throughout the hotel are unusually low.We had a regular room with a king bed on the fourth floor. The room was just average, clean enough and the bed was comfortable. The bathroom was TINY and there was a hair in the tub when we arrived (does housekeeping ever clean the tubs between guests?) It was rather tired looking and run down. Internet access was available in the room, but there was no refrigerator. The hotel does have a nice fitness room with the largest variety of equipment I've seen in a hotel, as well as a pool, half of which is indoor, half outdoor, and a hot tub. There is a guest laundry room on the second floor, with coin operated washers and dryers. There are two restaurants, The Harvest Grill, and a sports bar. We ate dinner in the Grill. The meal was not very good and the service was terrible. It took more than 40 minutes after ordering to be be served, with no apology or explanation from the waitress.My biggest complaint is the workmen who started working on a balcony outside our room at 8 am. They made a tremendous amount of crashing and banging noise and were still at it when we checked out. Unless you have to stay in this hotel because you are attending a meeting there, I would suggest staying elsewhere.	
